# Forge orchestration chooser

Default is **one Agent session, sequential tools**. Escalate only when the table says so. Prefer proposing the primitive (“I’ll `/loop` CI every 2m”) over silently babysitting.

| When | Use | Not |
|------|-----|-----|
| Single clear coding task, one checkout | This session | Parallel for its own sake |
| Ambiguous approach / big tradeoffs | Plan mode once, then Agent | N parallel guesses with no plan |
| Same prompt, compare models/approaches | `/best-of-n` (each gets a worktree) | Overwriting main with experiments |
| Independent tasks that edit the **same repo** | Separate worktrees / Agents Window agents (`/worktree`, `agent --worktree`) | Two agents on one dirty tree |
| Long unrelated jobs / leave the laptop | Cloud Agent / Agents Window Cloud | Blocking your only local session |
| Bounded research, explore, or review **inside** this chat | Subagent via `Task` (e.g. explore, bugbot, security-review) | Spawning worktrees for read-only digs |
| Async subtasks that **don’t** fight over files | `/multitask` | Multitask for conflicting edits |
| Polling / waiting (CI, deploy, digest) or recurring maintenance | `/loop` (`loop` skill) — fixed or dynamic | Sitting in one turn watching |
| Same mechanical change across many files/repos | Say so; fan out with worktrees or a scripted loop — there is no Cursor `/batch`; don’t invent one | One mega-diff across unrelated targets |
| PR merge-ready (comments, CI, conflicts) | `babysit` | Manual refresh forever |
| Substantive diff before done | `verify` + `review-bugbot` + `review-security` | “Looks fine” |

**Conflict rule:** if two streams would edit the same files → serialize or isolate with worktrees. Subagents/multitask are for non-colliding work.

**Tell the user** when you escalate (loop armed, worktree created, best-of-n started). Details: `forge-workflow` skill.
